article.headline: Campbell 86, Kennesaw 78
article.story: KENNESAW, Ga. (AP) -- Reggie Bishop and Maurice Latham each scored 17 points to lead a balanced attack that carried Campbell to an 86-78 victory over Kennesaw State on Saturday. The Camels (9-14, 8-8 Atlantic Sun) saw the Owls (12-14, 10-7) cut the lead to 44-43 early in the second half on a basket by Brent Ragsdale, but Campbell came back with six points in a row with 16 minutes left and Kennesaw never got closer than four points the rest of the way. Kennesaw's Ronell Wooten led all scorers with 27 points and 10 rebounds as the Owls played their second game in a row without leading scorer Golden Ingle. Ledell Eackles and Diego Aguiar added 13 points each and Jake Wohlfeil 10 for the Camels. Andre Morgan added 12 for Kennesaw.
